On May 26, 2009, the White House issued a media advisory stating that the President would be making an announcement at 10:15 AM EDT regarding his nomination for the Supreme Court. The event would be held in the East Room and would be open to the press. The pre-set time for the press was scheduled for 9:30 AM EDT, with the final gather time at 9:45 AM EDT at the North Doors of the Palm Room.